  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting\n\n3. Key Preventive Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Mandatory record-keeping\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Global Compliance:\n- Most countries have implemented comprehensive AML regulations\n- Regular updates to address emerging financial crime techniques\n- Increasing use of advanced technology for detection\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different financial sectors and jurisdictions.",
